== Serenades, divertimenti, and other instrumental works ==
The production for instrumental ensembles includes several divertimenti, cassations, notturni, serenades, marches, dances, and a quodlibet, besides, of course, his symphonies. Mozart&#x27;s production for orchestra is written for string ensembles (like the early Divertimenti K. 136–138), as well as for wind ensembles and the varied combinations of strings and winds.

=== Serenades ===
*Cassation in D major (Serenade No. 1), K. 100/62a (1769)
