<doc id="1016457" wikidata="Q8016656" url="?curid=1016457" title="William Pattison (poet)">
<text>William Pattison (1706–1727) was a short-lived English poet, now mostly remembered for his erotic poems. Pattison was admitted to Sidney Sussex College, Cambridge in 1724, but in 1726 left for a literary life in London without taking a degree. He was supported by the London bookseller Edmund Curll, one of Alexander Pope&#x27;s foes, who printed his collected works in 1728. The second volume was &quot;Cupid&#x27;s metamorphoses or, love in all shapes&quot;; including a &quot;Panegyrick on Cundums&quot;.

